  m_Name: Wax Seal
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Wax Seal
  description: 'Wax seals were used to secure letters and documents by stamping hot
    wax with a metal crest or symbol. They acted as both a signature and a form of
    protection, as breaking the seal showed if a message had been opened or tampered
    with. Wax seals were commonly used by noble families and officials to authenticate
    important correspondence. '
  illustration: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 01aed0f94f7f67e4fb1ffa4b88230269, type: 3}
